captions.translation: [JIUTAI] At that time, Genji
the Middle Captain as he was called,
shared the grass pillow of this "evenig face" for a brief rest.
Through the night they heard from next door
captions.transcription: Tada karibushi no yo mo sugara,

captions.translation: a pilgrim's voice in prayer
about ascending the sacred peak at Miyoshino.
"Save us, holy guide of the way in the future, Maitreya Buddha!", he chanted.
Even now this service has brought back the memory
captions.transcription: Ima mo ta'toki okuyō ni so no toki no omoi

captions.translation: of that time and unmittingly tears dampen my sleeves.
captions.transcription: iderarete sozoro ni nururu tamoto ka na.

captions.translation: But more than that, I cannot forget the evening
when Genji first saw this house.
captions.transcription: Genji kono yado wo misome tamaishi iutsukata.

captions.translation: Beckoning to Koremitsu,
"Pick that flower for me," he ordered.
On a white fan, its edges perfumed with incense,
captions.transcription: Shiroki ōgi no tsumaitō kogashi tarishini.

captions.translation: the flower was picked and presented.
[SHITE] Genji, gazing at it intently,
[JIUTAI] "Of you passing in the distance..." he asked
captions.transcription: [JIUTAI]  Uchi watasu o-chikatahito ni tō totemo.

captions.translation: and if I had not answered about the flower
captions.transcription: Sore sono hana to kotaezu wa.

captions.translation: forever we must have remained strangers. We were brought together
captions.transcription: Tsui ni shirademo arubeki ni ai ni o-ōgi wo te ni fururu.

captions.translation: by the fan touched by our hands, in a joyous pledge of love.
If from time to time
I visit this dwelling of a homeless fishergirl
captions.transcription: Sadamenu ama no kono yado no.

captions.translation: not knowing the owner's name, I hope
to be as white foam finding at last the shore, he thought,
and composed a poem.
